== Events == * {{ill|Daibō|ja|大宝|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} [[702]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Bunmu Tennō|ja|文武天皇|12=draft}} established Japan’s first nationally unified system of measurement (度量衡).{{要出典|date=2021-02}} * {{ill|Hōei|ja|宝永|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1708]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|12=draft}}) – A great fire (the “Hōei no Taika”) broke out in Kyoto, destroying approximately 14,000 houses. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1831]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft}}) – Osaka Machi Bugyō, Shinmi Masaji, dredged the sediment at the mouth of the old Yodogawa (安治川) to build Tenpō-zan.
== Births == * {{ill|Kangen|ja|寛延|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft}} [[1246]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Nikkō Tennō|ja|日興|12=draft}}, a monk (died [[1333]])<ref>{{Sfn | 宗旨建立750th year 慶祝記念出版委員会 | 2002 | p = 187 }}</ref>.
== Deaths == * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft}} [[1858]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōhara Yūgaku|ja|大原幽学|12=draft}}, an agricultural scholar (born [[1797]]).
